HEADWORD: Lycanthropy
<hw>Ly*can"thro*py</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/: cf.
F. <ets>lycanthropie</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The supposed act of
turning one's self or another person into a wolf.</def>
<rj><au>Lowell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A kind of erratic melancholy, in
which the patient imagines himself a wolf, and imitates the actions of
that animal.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lycee</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>lycee</ent>⟦br⟧
